cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses a video segmentation example and the challenges of mapping volumetric data to the desired output. It also involves neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The paper also discusses memory requirements, which suggests it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new layer structure, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The use of linear algebraic notation and tensor flattening could also suggest it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the video segmentation example could also suggest it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
